These are the Main Filters:
===============================================================
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_mem*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_proc*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_mount*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_dis*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_kernel*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_default_ipv4*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_hostname*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_architecture*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_interfaces*'
ansible localhost -m setup -a 'filter=ansible_dns*'
===============================================================

üñ•Ô∏è CPU Info
Fact	Description
ansible_facts.processor[0]	CPU model name
ansible_facts.processor_cores	Cores per socket
ansible_facts.processor_count	Number of physical CPUs
ansible_facts.processor_threads_per_core	Threads per core

üíæ Memory Info
Fact	Description	Unit
ansible_facts.memtotal_mb	Total physical memory	MB
ansible_facts.memfree_mb	Free physical memory	MB
ansible_facts.swaptotal_mb	Total swap memory	MB
ansible_facts.swapfree_mb	Free swap memory	MB

üíΩ Disk / Mount Info
Fact	Description
ansible_facts.mounts	List of mounted partitions (with size, device, fstype, etc.)
ansible_facts.mounts[0].mount	Mount point (e.g., /)
ansible_facts.mounts[0].size_total	Partition size (bytes)
ansible_facts.mounts[0].size_available	Available space (bytes)

üåê Network Info
Fact	Description
ansible_facts.hostname	System hostname
ansible_facts.domain	Domain name
ansible_facts.fqdn	Fully qualified domain name
ansible_facts.interfaces	List of network interfaces
ansible_facts.default_ipv4.address	Default IPv4 address
ansible_facts.default_ipv4.interface	Default network interface
ansible_facts.all_ipv4_addresses	All IPv4 addresses

üíª OS & Platform
Fact	Description
ansible_facts.distribution	OS name (e.g., Ubuntu, CentOS)
ansible_facts.distribution_version	Version number
ansible_facts.os_family	OS family (RedHat, Debian, etc.)
ansible_facts.architecture	CPU architecture (x86_64, arm64, etc.)
ansible_facts.kernel	Kernel name
ansible_facts.kernel_version	Kernel version

üß≠ Time & Uptime
Fact	Description
ansible_facts.date_time.date	Current date
ansible_facts.date_time.time	Current time
ansible_facts.uptime_seconds	Uptime in seconds
ansible_facts.uptime_days	Uptime in days

üì¶ Package Manager Info
Fact	Description
ansible_facts.pkg_mgr	Default package manager (apt, yum, dnf, etc.)

- All memory values are in MB.
- Disk sizes are in **bytes**; convert to GB with:  size | int // 1024**3
- Always use `| default('value')` for safer templates.

